Question: cōnservō, cōnservāre
Answer: to preserve, conserve, maintain(a stronger form of servāre)
Name: cōnservāre

Question: errō, errāre
Answer: to wonder, err, go astray, make a mistake, be mistaken
Name: errāre

Question: habeō, habēre
Answer: to have, hold, possess; consider, regard
Name: habēre

Question: maneō, manēre or remaneō, remanēre
Answer: to remain, stay, stay behind, abide, continue
Name: manēre or remanēre

Question: possum, posse
Answer: to be able, can, could, have power
Name: posse

Question: salveō, salvēre
Answer: to be well, be in good health
Name: salvēre

Question: valeō, valēre
Answer: to be strong, have power, be well
Name: valēre

Question: agō, agere
Answer: to drive, lead, do, act, pass

Question: gerō, gerere
Answer: to carry; carry on, manage, conduct, wage, accomplish, perform
Name: gerō, gerere

Question: dīcō, dīcere
Answer: to say, tell, speak; name, call
Name: dīcō, dīcere

Question: fugiō, fugere
Answer: to flee, hurry away; escape; go into exile; avoid, shun
Name: fugiō, fugere
